\subsection{Dataset}

A synthetic dataset was created to simulate healthcare navigation scenarios. Provider attributes include specialty, treatments, insurance plans, languages, location, and availability.

\section{Results}

Five test scenarios were evaluated, including perfect matches, insurance relaxation, symptom-based specialty inference, no-match cases, and ranking differentiation.

The system successfully handled all scenarios and produced reasonable provider recommendations.

\section{Discussion}

The Appy Health prototype demonstrates the feasibility of conversational AI for healthcare navigation. By combining natural language symptom collection with structured provider matching, the system can guide patients toward appropriate providers.

Future work will integrate real provider datasets and implement the planned RAG-based retrieval framework.

